The Federal Government in its effort to enhance the livelihood of Persons Living with Disabilities (PLWDs) in Nigeria, has revealed that it is currently working on a national roadmap on local production of assistive technologies for persons with disabilities (PWDs).  The Minister of Humanitarian Affairs Disaster Management and Social Development, Sadiya Umar Farouq represented by the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry Bashir Nura Alkali who made this known today in Abuja said the roadmap shall enhance the guidance for production, procurement and distribution of the products.  While he noted that the World Health Organization (WHO) estimates that over one billion people worldwide, majority of whom are PWDs needs more assistive devises, noted that the number in need of assistive devices is projected to increase to two billion by 2050.